# Anti-Freeze Agent Execution Policy

## Goal
Keep Agent responsive during heavy tasks while still allowing parallel work.

## Mandatory Execution Limits
- Default maximum parallel subagents per batch: **4**
- If user explicitly includes `#max-parallel`, raise to **8** subagents per batch.
- Do not launch a new batch until the current batch has completed and been reported.
- Prefer batches that finish within **2-6 minutes**.
- If a task is expected to exceed 6 minutes, split it into multiple batches.

## Long-Task Handling
- For deep audits, run by modules (for example: backend, frontend, android, ci) instead of one global sweep.
- Avoid mixing heavy shell commands and many subagents in the same batch.
- Never run more than one heavyweight shell test command at the same time.

## User Interaction Safety
- If user sends a new request while a heavy batch is running, first summarize completed results from finished jobs, then start the next batch.
- Explicitly ask user whether to continue with the next batch only after reporting current batch results.

## Recommended Batch Template
- Batch A: backend + security + data integrity + ci/deploy
- Batch B: frontend + android + tests + docs drift

## Max-Parallel Mode
- Trigger phrase: `#max-parallel`
- In this mode:
  - Run up to 8 subagents concurrently
  - Keep shell heavy commands to max 2 at a time
  - Return one consolidated report after all subagents finish

## Output Style
- Report per batch with:
  1) completed jobs
  2) failed/interrupted jobs
  3) next batch proposal
